WEBVTT

00:01.390 --> 00:03.693
LOGAN:
<i>Previously on</i>
Wolverine and the X-Men:

00:03.695 --> 00:05.360
[GRUNTING]

00:05.362 --> 00:06.762
Charles.

00:08.464 --> 00:10.467
BEAST:
<i>The explosion</i>
<i>was indeed centered</i>

00:10.469 --> 00:12.636
<i>on Charles's position.</i>

00:14.505 --> 00:17.040
SENATOR KELLY:
<i>The Brotherhood is now</i>
<i>threatening me.</i>

00:17.042 --> 00:20.078
Mutants are
a danger to us all.

00:20.080 --> 00:22.079
Isn't it enough
he gets our money, Dad?

00:22.081 --> 00:23.849
I have to
cheer him on too?

00:23.851 --> 00:26.351
That man is
a champion of the people.

00:26.353 --> 00:28.587
Some people,
not all of us.

00:28.589 --> 00:30.590
There's a war coming

00:30.592 --> 00:31.491
<i>and I want you with me.</i>

00:31.493 --> 00:32.491
What's next?

00:32.494 --> 00:35.095
We bring back
the X-Men.

00:35.097 --> 00:36.430
[GASPS]

00:36.432 --> 00:37.998
You comin' or what?

00:38.000 --> 00:39.132
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

00:42.337 --> 00:44.206
[GRUNTS]
So without Jean,

00:44.208 --> 00:46.208
there's no one
worth fighting for.

00:46.210 --> 00:48.777
Heh. So much for the big hero.

00:51.181 --> 00:53.749
Rogue's joined them.
What? Are you sure?

00:53.751 --> 00:56.318
WARREN:
<i>Positive.</i>
<i>They broke into our house</i>

00:56.320 --> 00:58.688
<i>so she could siphon</i>
<i>information from my father.</i>

00:58.690 --> 01:00.924
ROGUE:
<i>They're going to hit</i>
<i>Senator Kelly</i>

01:00.926 --> 01:02.392
<i>at the press conference.</i>

01:04.863 --> 01:06.598
WOLVERINE:
<i>They're not here.</i>

01:06.600 --> 01:08.867
[GRUNTS]

01:08.869 --> 01:10.067
We were set up.

01:10.069 --> 01:11.270
Logan, you tried

01:11.272 --> 01:13.138
to save a man
who hates you.

01:13.140 --> 01:16.475
That is exactly what
Charles Xavier would have done.

01:19.380 --> 01:21.681
[♪♪♪]

01:23.000 --> 01:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:34.563 --> 01:37.065
And the finish work
should be done by morning.

01:37.067 --> 01:40.269
By afternoon you'll have
your furniture.

01:40.271 --> 01:43.239
So that's the top-to-bottom
tour. What do you think?

01:43.241 --> 01:45.543
You don't look happy.
Why aren't you happy?

01:45.545 --> 01:47.544
Uh. Sorry, Warren.

01:47.546 --> 01:50.180
You know.
New building, old ghosts.

01:50.182 --> 01:51.982
But thanks, man.

01:51.984 --> 01:54.585
Mm. Thank dear old dad.
It's his money.

01:54.587 --> 01:56.454
Second thought,
don't thank him.

01:56.456 --> 01:58.589
For some reason
he's under the impression

01:58.591 --> 02:00.860
this is just
a regular prep school.

02:00.862 --> 02:03.229
Good thing the walls
are nice and high.

02:03.231 --> 02:05.631
Now to fill
the campus, huh?

02:05.633 --> 02:07.600
Which brings up
a question:

02:07.602 --> 02:11.003
Rogue. You plan on trying
to get her back?

02:11.006 --> 02:14.342
Nope, not after
she hung us out to dry.

02:14.344 --> 02:15.843
Next move is hers.

02:19.849 --> 02:21.550
Hello.

02:21.552 --> 02:24.353
I'm Warren.
Emma Frost.

02:24.355 --> 02:26.188
Yeah, I know
who you are.

02:26.190 --> 02:29.359
Question is,
why are you here?

02:29.361 --> 02:31.294
Right to the point.
I like that.

02:31.296 --> 02:34.031
I've decided
to join the X-Men.

02:34.033 --> 02:36.300
You decided?
Hmm.

02:36.302 --> 02:39.036
Well, here's my decision:

02:39.038 --> 02:41.672
No.

02:41.674 --> 02:43.542
If you know who I am,
then you're aware

02:43.544 --> 02:46.711
I never come
empty-handed.

02:46.713 --> 02:50.049
What could you possibly offer
the X-Men besides trouble?

02:50.051 --> 02:53.152
I can find
Professor Xavier for you.

02:54.722 --> 02:57.057
[♪♪♪]

02:59.995 --> 03:01.996
[WHIMPERS]

03:04.766 --> 03:06.500
[GROWLING]

03:32.499 --> 03:34.299
[GROWLS]

03:40.141 --> 03:42.041
Maybe she's telling
the truth.

03:42.043 --> 03:45.145
Working some angle
is more like it.

03:45.147 --> 03:47.214
Anyway, thanks again,
Warren.

03:54.323 --> 03:57.226
I understand
you have some information

03:57.228 --> 03:58.561
about Professor Xavier.

03:58.563 --> 04:00.929
We'll see about that.

04:00.931 --> 04:04.034
This is Emma Frost,
former headmistress

04:04.036 --> 04:06.437
of the Massachusetts
Academy.

04:06.439 --> 04:09.239
Hm. Never heard of it.

04:09.241 --> 04:10.842
It was a secret
little school

04:10.844 --> 04:13.678
that tried to imitate
the Xavier Institute.

04:13.680 --> 04:15.480
I didn't realize
Charles Xavier

04:15.482 --> 04:18.517
held a monopoly
on helping young mutants.

04:18.519 --> 04:20.720
Yeah, but you didn't
help them.

04:20.721 --> 04:22.555
You taught them
how to bully people.

04:22.557 --> 04:25.492
Regardless of how some
of my students may have behaved,

04:25.494 --> 04:27.860
I built my school for all
of the right reasons.

04:27.862 --> 04:30.832
Yet you closed it down.
Why?

04:30.834 --> 04:33.635
That is not your concern.

04:33.637 --> 04:35.936
Then we're through talking.
There's the door.

04:38.074 --> 04:40.241
My students
suffered greatly

04:40.243 --> 04:43.379
at the hands
of antimutant crusaders.

04:43.381 --> 04:44.848
It's difficult
to carry on teaching

04:44.850 --> 04:46.916
when your children are taken
from you.

04:49.086 --> 04:51.053
So I closed my school

04:51.055 --> 04:52.890
and tried to go it alone.

04:52.892 --> 04:54.358
But I miss teaching.

04:54.360 --> 04:56.193
I miss being
part of a team.

04:56.195 --> 04:58.129
But why this team?

04:58.131 --> 05:00.198
Because we need
each other.

05:00.200 --> 05:04.036
Heh. That's one big
assumption, lady.

05:04.038 --> 05:05.738
The simple fact is

05:05.740 --> 05:08.407
you cannot operate Cerebro
without a telepath.

05:08.409 --> 05:11.343
So that's what
this is about.

05:11.345 --> 05:14.181
You want access
to Cerebro.

05:14.183 --> 05:18.184
It is your best hope
of finding missing mutants.

05:18.186 --> 05:20.355
Yeah, well, sorry.

05:20.357 --> 05:22.090
It was destroyed
in the blast.

05:23.292 --> 05:25.593
Its repairs
are nearly complete.

05:25.595 --> 05:28.030
Ring me when it's ready.

05:28.032 --> 05:29.698
[♪♪♪]

05:31.968 --> 05:33.837
[CHUCKLES]

05:35.940 --> 05:38.375
She's a telepath,
remember?

05:38.377 --> 05:39.977
She knows
what you're thinking.

05:43.381 --> 05:44.782
She's after something.

05:44.784 --> 05:46.651
I don't dispute that,

05:46.653 --> 05:50.189
but if she can indeed
locate Charles or Jean,

05:50.191 --> 05:52.891
it would be foolish
not to explore this option.

05:52.893 --> 05:54.293
Yeah, I know.

05:54.295 --> 05:56.162
Then where
are you going?

05:56.164 --> 05:59.765
To put a certain young genius
back on Cerebro duty.

06:01.469 --> 06:03.236
Forge?

06:06.308 --> 06:08.543
[♪♪♪]

06:09.378 --> 06:10.979
[GRUNTS]

06:10.981 --> 06:14.483
Forge, this is me
not laughing.

06:32.471 --> 06:33.738
[GROWLS]

06:33.740 --> 06:36.308
Logan, where'd you
come from?

06:38.645 --> 06:40.312
[GROWLS]

06:40.314 --> 06:41.514
Oh, man.

06:41.516 --> 06:44.217
<i>My Danger Room.</i>

06:44.219 --> 06:45.619
<i>How could you?</i>

06:45.621 --> 06:47.653
I wasn't even finished
and now--

06:47.655 --> 06:51.158
Oh, I gotta start
completely over.

06:51.160 --> 06:53.227
Forget the danger room.

06:53.229 --> 06:55.362
I need you back
on Cerebro.

06:55.364 --> 06:57.699
You pull me
off Cerebro,

06:57.701 --> 06:59.300
you put me
on the blackbird.

06:59.302 --> 07:02.036
You pull me off that
and put me in the war room.

07:02.038 --> 07:03.773
Now I'm
on the Danger Room,

07:03.775 --> 07:06.342
and you want me
back on Cerebro?

07:06.344 --> 07:09.111
It's how we're gonna
find Charles.

07:09.113 --> 07:11.749
Xavier? Oh.
I'll get right on it.

07:14.285 --> 07:16.354
Ms. Frost, I'd like
to introduce Forge,

07:16.356 --> 07:18.322
the young man
responsible for--

07:18.324 --> 07:21.492
Let's just dispense with
pleasantries and get on with it.

07:23.597 --> 07:26.365
You're on hallowed
ground here, lady.

07:26.367 --> 07:28.100
Don't make me
regret this.

07:28.102 --> 07:31.205
Perhaps you'd rather
I didn't find the professor.

07:31.207 --> 07:33.273
You enjoy being in charge,
don't you?

07:36.677 --> 07:38.212
Okay, go ahead
and lay your--

07:38.214 --> 07:40.548
Please. I read your mind
on the way in.

07:44.687 --> 07:46.421
[WHIRRING]

08:04.209 --> 08:07.278
[GASPS]

08:07.280 --> 08:09.648
Where is he?

08:09.650 --> 08:11.951
Genosha.

08:17.124 --> 08:19.593
BEAST:
<i>It's a volatile</i>
<i>situation, Logan.</i>

08:19.595 --> 08:22.929
I think it best if we try and
make contact with Magneto first.

08:22.931 --> 08:24.430
Believe me,

08:24.432 --> 08:27.135
I intend to make
contact with him,

08:27.137 --> 08:29.070
and it's long overdue.

08:29.072 --> 08:30.872
Logan, wait.

08:30.874 --> 08:32.241
Don't you get it, Hank?

08:32.243 --> 08:35.910
This means Magneto was
responsible for that explosion!

08:35.913 --> 08:39.482
That is not supported by any
evidence I've collected.

08:39.484 --> 08:42.219
There were no fluctuations
in the magnetic field.

08:42.221 --> 08:45.289
So before we accuse him,
we need to--

08:45.291 --> 08:47.225
We know he's got Charles,

08:47.227 --> 08:49.160
and that's what matters.

08:54.300 --> 08:55.734
[STATIC HISSES]

08:57.637 --> 09:00.040
[DOOR OPENS]

09:00.042 --> 09:02.808
Holster those eyebeams,
frat boy.

09:02.810 --> 09:04.544
There's nothing else
you could say, Logan.

09:04.546 --> 09:06.179
I'm not comin' back.

09:06.181 --> 09:08.349
Magneto's got
the professor.

09:08.351 --> 09:10.184
And Jean?

09:10.186 --> 09:12.953
No, just Charles.

09:12.955 --> 09:14.555
Now are you in?

09:18.561 --> 09:20.263
[♪♪♪]

09:24.101 --> 09:25.634
Hangar lights on.

09:29.907 --> 09:31.374
Aww!

09:31.376 --> 09:34.044
Oh, where'd you guys
come from?

09:34.046 --> 09:36.047
Just tell me
she'll fly.

09:36.049 --> 09:38.015
Oh, yeah.

09:38.017 --> 09:40.886
Absolutely.
Pretty sure.

09:40.888 --> 09:42.755
Hmm, perhaps we should wait

09:42.757 --> 09:44.556
until Forge completes
the repairs and--

09:44.558 --> 09:47.694
We leave now.
Forge, climb in.

09:47.696 --> 09:49.629
Your job is
to keep us in the air.

09:59.708 --> 10:03.078
Hm. Wolverine's more desperate
than I thought.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.879
And she is...?

10:04.881 --> 10:06.581
Temporary.

10:17.094 --> 10:19.262
[ENGINE HUMMING]

10:27.073 --> 10:29.308
FORGE:
<i>The orbital gimbals</i>
<i>keep sticking.</i>

10:29.310 --> 10:31.277
Hand me
the carbon atomizer.

10:31.279 --> 10:34.146
Here, but I doubt that's
impacting your vector phase.

10:34.148 --> 10:36.883
Seems more of a rotational
override problem.

10:36.885 --> 10:38.251
Hand me
the expansion jammer.

10:38.253 --> 10:40.254
Careful.
It's fully charged.

10:40.256 --> 10:42.656
Whoa.
Sorry, my fault.

10:42.658 --> 10:43.958
[GROWLS]

10:43.960 --> 10:46.060
Just tell me you got
the autopilot working

10:46.062 --> 10:48.062
so I can get out
of this chair.

10:48.064 --> 10:50.465
We're still trying to get
the stealth generator online.

10:50.467 --> 10:54.003
Otherwise, Genosha is going
to see us coming miles away.

10:54.005 --> 10:56.372
Here, don't let this
touch anything.

10:56.374 --> 10:58.174
[SIGHS]

11:04.883 --> 11:06.284
Hey.

11:06.286 --> 11:08.019
Would you wake up already?

11:08.021 --> 11:09.753
Hmm? What?

11:09.755 --> 11:11.189
Are we there?
No,

11:11.191 --> 11:13.392
but you're freezing
in your sleep again.

11:13.394 --> 11:14.759
[YAWNS]

11:14.761 --> 11:16.061
Sorry.

11:16.063 --> 11:18.197
And how can you nap
at a time like this?

11:18.199 --> 11:19.698
The jet's falling apart,

11:19.700 --> 11:21.401
we're going up
against Magneto,

11:21.403 --> 11:24.036
and did I mention that the jet's
falling apart?

11:24.038 --> 11:27.107
The jet'll be fine.
And who cares about Magneto?

11:27.109 --> 11:29.043
Wolverine's got
his number.

11:29.045 --> 11:30.611
Maybe, but what about

11:30.613 --> 11:33.247
an entire island
of his mutant followers?

11:33.249 --> 11:35.050
Oh, yeah.

11:41.391 --> 11:43.893
You'd like to ask me
about Jean,

11:43.895 --> 11:46.230
so do it.

11:46.232 --> 11:48.832
Would you have detected her
if she was in Genosha?

11:48.834 --> 11:50.467
Yes.

11:50.469 --> 11:53.171
And given time, I could locate
her wherever she is,

11:53.173 --> 11:55.340
assuming I'm around.

11:55.342 --> 11:57.775
What's that supposed to mean?
Ask Logan.

11:57.777 --> 12:00.378
If he has his way,
I'll be gone by tomorrow.

12:08.722 --> 12:11.391
Fog. Maybe we got lucky.

12:13.828 --> 12:17.231
BEAST:
<i>It only circles the island.</i>
<i>It doesn't cover it.</i>

12:17.233 --> 12:19.000
Then what's
our stealth status?

12:19.002 --> 12:20.735
We're concealed
from their radar,

12:20.737 --> 12:22.904
but visually we
stick out like a--

12:22.906 --> 12:26.743
Well, like a black jet
in a bright sky.

12:26.745 --> 12:28.377
Forge?

12:28.379 --> 12:30.413
Almost got it.
One more second.

12:30.415 --> 12:32.114
We're out of time.

12:34.152 --> 12:35.452
Okay, try it now.

12:47.067 --> 12:49.401
[♪♪♪]

13:07.456 --> 13:10.658
SHADOWCAT [ON RADIO]:
<i>Okay, all clear.</i>

13:10.660 --> 13:12.794
You're sure about this?

13:16.700 --> 13:19.402
SHADOWCAT:
It's like an iron
maze down here.

13:19.404 --> 13:21.271
We're definitely
on his turf.

13:21.273 --> 13:23.273
Com-links on.
We're splitting up.

13:50.906 --> 13:52.239
[EXHALES]

14:10.061 --> 14:13.163
[GRUNTING]

14:28.182 --> 14:29.415
[YELLS]

14:38.827 --> 14:41.296
Hello, Wolverine.

14:45.368 --> 14:48.771
A man with metal bones
should have more sense

14:48.773 --> 14:51.041
than to break
into my house.

14:51.043 --> 14:53.811
Ugh. What about my house?

14:53.813 --> 14:55.813
You blew it up.

14:55.815 --> 14:58.683
I'm offended by your accusation.
[ICE CRACKLING]

14:58.685 --> 15:01.986
Ah. I believe that's the sound
of your cavalry.

15:01.988 --> 15:03.187
[GRUNTING]

15:07.994 --> 15:10.429
You're done, Magneto!

15:38.495 --> 15:39.763
Agh!

15:49.175 --> 15:51.543
Without his helmet,
he's mine.

15:51.545 --> 15:53.712
[SCREAMS]

16:08.263 --> 16:10.832
SHADOWCAT:
That's not going
to work on me!

16:10.834 --> 16:12.600
It doesn't have to.

16:12.602 --> 16:14.536
And I suggest
you hold on to this.

16:16.939 --> 16:19.008
[GASPS]

16:19.010 --> 16:20.777
We're not looking
for trouble.

16:20.779 --> 16:23.446
We just came
for Charles.

16:23.448 --> 16:25.948
Ah, but you did come
looking for trouble.

16:25.950 --> 16:28.152
And you found it.

16:28.154 --> 16:29.453
[METALLIC DRONE]

16:29.455 --> 16:30.855
[GRUNTING]

16:30.857 --> 16:32.757
[METAL CREAKING]

16:35.161 --> 16:36.194
Wait.

16:36.196 --> 16:39.397
Don't do this.
It's my fault.

16:39.399 --> 16:40.465
It is, isn't it?

16:40.467 --> 16:42.134
And what would
Charles think

16:42.136 --> 16:43.937
of this little
commando raid of yours?

16:43.939 --> 16:46.105
I daresay
he wouldn't approve.

16:46.107 --> 16:48.074
We know he's here.

16:48.076 --> 16:50.677
Just take us to him.

16:50.679 --> 16:53.380
All you had to do
was ask.

16:53.382 --> 16:55.216
[♪♪♪]

17:16.842 --> 17:18.742
He appeared on my island

17:18.744 --> 17:20.042
one week ago.
[GASPS]

17:23.215 --> 17:24.616
[HEART MONITOR BEEPING]

17:24.617 --> 17:26.919
I found him like this
on our coastline,

17:26.921 --> 17:28.354
sprawled on the rocks.

17:28.356 --> 17:29.955
Professor.

17:38.133 --> 17:40.334
He has no brain activity.

17:42.871 --> 17:45.340
Charles is a dear friend.

17:45.342 --> 17:47.475
All I've been doing
is caring for him.

17:47.477 --> 17:49.844
More like
keeping an eye on him.

17:49.846 --> 17:52.981
We both know
you're afraid of Charles.

17:52.983 --> 17:54.250
[GROWLS]

17:54.252 --> 17:57.453
The question is, will you let us
take him home?

17:58.923 --> 18:00.924
[GROWLS]

18:00.926 --> 18:02.692
Of course.

18:02.694 --> 18:05.896
You are his children.
His place is with you.

18:05.898 --> 18:07.898
However, I wish
you would consider

18:07.900 --> 18:10.869
making Genosha
your home.

18:10.871 --> 18:13.005
No more violence,
no more--

18:13.007 --> 18:15.441
Yeah, we've seen
the billboards.

18:15.443 --> 18:17.076
Thanks, but no thanks.

18:17.078 --> 18:20.314
The offer stands.

18:20.316 --> 18:23.383
Only next time you decide
to drop by, Wolverine,

18:23.385 --> 18:26.487
use the front door.

18:37.132 --> 18:39.369
[HEART MONITOR BEEPING]

18:50.048 --> 18:52.583
We'll find a way
to bring you back, Charles,

18:52.585 --> 18:55.753
no matter what it takes
or how long.

18:55.755 --> 18:57.923
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

19:03.163 --> 19:04.630
What is that sound?

19:04.632 --> 19:06.800
It's like
someone whispering.

19:06.802 --> 19:08.702
[WHISPERING CONTINUES]

19:08.704 --> 19:11.804
Correct me if I'm wrong,
but that sounds a lot like...

19:11.806 --> 19:13.040
Charles.

19:13.042 --> 19:16.477
XAVIER [WHISPERING]:
<i>I'm here.</i>

19:16.479 --> 19:18.279
This is impossible.

19:28.292 --> 19:31.695
Charles,
is that really you?

19:31.697 --> 19:33.864
Yes, Logan.

19:33.866 --> 19:35.666
What's happening?

19:35.668 --> 19:37.835
Who did this to you?

19:37.837 --> 19:39.837
I wish I knew.

19:39.839 --> 19:42.174
I remember nothing.

19:42.176 --> 19:44.843
Charles, there was
an unexplained blast

19:44.845 --> 19:46.078
at the institute.

19:46.080 --> 19:48.982
You've been missing,
and Jean still is.

19:48.984 --> 19:52.785
My X-Men, time is limited.

19:52.787 --> 19:55.856
I come to you
with an urgent message.

19:55.858 --> 19:58.125
Come to us?
From where?

19:58.127 --> 19:59.994
The future.

19:59.996 --> 20:01.796
The coma you see me in
right now,

20:01.798 --> 20:04.733
it will last
for 20 years.

20:04.735 --> 20:07.069
I've just awoken
from it,

20:07.071 --> 20:10.239
and the world I've found
is a nightmare.

20:10.241 --> 20:11.807
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

20:11.809 --> 20:14.510
[DISTANT EXPLOSIONS]

